iese These und zeigt, dass im Zentrum von Adornos Kritischer Theorie der Gesellschaft eine Kritik nicht nur der politischen Ökonomie steht, sondern eine von Ökonomie überhaupt.  aRight up to the present day, there is a widespread belief that the recourse to Marx - and in particular Marx's critique of political economy - in Adorno's work represents a relic from stages in his theoretical development which were quickly overcome. By way of relevant, to date largely unpublished texts and documents, the author refutes this thesis, and shows that at the center of Adorno's critical theory of society stands a critique not just of political economy, but one of economy as such.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 4aDeutsche Philosophiegeschichte. 4aGesellschaft. 4aMarxismus. 4aPhilosophie. 4aPolitik. 4aPolitische Philosophie. 4aSozialphilosophie. 4aTausch. 7aPHILOSOPHY / History & Surveys / Modern.2bisacsh  aGerman History of Philosophy.  aPhilosophy.  aPolitical Philosophy.  aPolitics.  aSocial Philosophy.  aSociety.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2015z978311070098508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2016z9783110485103oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2016z9783110485301oZDB-23-DPH08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPP Plus eBook-Package 2015z978311070099208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Complete eBook Package 2014-2016z9783110489842oZDB-23-TGP40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783839434437zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839434437423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839434437/original  a978-3-11-070098-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2015b2015  a978-3-11-070099-2  